Profile: With over 13 years of experience, Atin-Atehan brings a wealth of culinary expertise to every dish. Specializing in homecooked Filipino cuisine, Atin-Atehan infuses each recipe with tradition and flavor. From birthdays to welcoming events, Atin-Atehan has catered and cooked for a variety of special occasions, creating memorable dining experiences for all guests. Atin-Atehan's passion for cooking shines through in every dish, ensuring that each bite is filled with love and authenticity. With a dedication to quality and authenticity, Atin-Atehan continues to delight customers with their delicious Filipino fare. Atin-Atehan's commitment to providing exceptional service and flavorful food has earned them a loyal following over the years. Atin-Atehan's extensive experience and expertise in Filipino cuisine make them a trusted choice for catering and event cooking. From intimate gatherings to large events, Atin-Atehan's culinary creations are always a highlight, leaving guests satisfied and coming back for more. Atin-Atehan's dedication to using fresh, high-quality ingredients ensures that every dish is bursting with flavor and authenticity. With a focus on showcasing the rich culinary heritage of the Philippines, Atin-Atehan brings a taste of home to every event they cater. Atin-Atehan's culinary journey reflects a deep-rooted passion for Filipino flavors and culinary traditions. Through years of experience, Atin-Atehan has mastered the art of blending traditional Filipino recipes with innovative cooking techniques. Atin-Atehan takes pride in delivering not just meals but unforgettable dining experiences infused with warmth and hospitality. From their humble beginnings to becoming a sought-after name in the culinary industry, Atin-Atehan's commitment to excellence remains unwavering.
Description: Lengua Estofado, which translates to tongue (lengua) stew (estofado) in Spanish, is a Filipino delicacy with heavy colonial influence. Adapted from Andalusian-style cooking, it's a type of braised dish where ox tongue is cooked low and slow in a rich tomato sauce seasoned with vinegar, soy sauce, and aromatics.
Pork Cordon Bleu is a classic comfort dish made with pork loin that's been pounded thin, stuffed with ham and cheese, then breaded and cooked to golden perfection.

Rellenong Manok is a classic Filipino dish that translates to stuffed chicken. It is made by deboning a whole chicken, marinating it, and then stuffing it with a flavorful mixture. The stuffing typically includes ground meat, vegetables (such as carrots, bell peppers, and peas), raisins, and sometimes hard-boiled eggs.

Chicken Crepe is a savory Filipino dish where thin crepes are filled with a flavorful chicken mixture. The crepes are typically made from a simple batter of flour, eggs, milk, and butter, cooked into thin pancakes.
Fish salad is a delightful appetizer or light meal, perfect for those who love bold and tangy tastes. The fish meat is semi-cooked by the acids in vinegar and calamansi or lemon juice.
Mango Buko Mallow Delight is a delightful Filipino dessert that combines the tropical flavors of mango, young coconut (buko), and sweetened cream.
Sinangag, also known as Filipino Garlic Fried Rice, is a popular dish in Filipino cuisine. It’s made by stir-frying leftover rice with fragrant garlic.
Coca-Cola, often referred to as Coke, is a carbonated soft drink with a cola flavor. It is often described as having a smoother, more caramel-like flavor.
Baked Spareribs with Mushroom Gravy is a delightful Filipino dish that combines succulent pork spareribs with a rich and savory mushroom sauce.

Paella is a vibrant Filipino rice dish infused with saffron, tender chicken, smoky chorizo, and a medley of seafood. The golden-hued rice takes center stage, making it a showstopper for special occasions.

Chicken Galantina is a delightful Filipino holiday dish, Chicken Galantina features a deboned whole chicken stuffed with a flavorful mixture of ground pork, ham, Vienna sausage, raisins, and hard-boiled eggs.

Dish Name: Baked Fish Fillet with Cheese Sauce
Description: Baked Fish Fillet with Cheese Sauce is a dish featuring flaky fish fillets baked to perfection and topped with a decadent cheese sauce.  A delightful balance of cheesy goodness and delicate fish flavor.

Chicken Potato Salad is an easy Filipino favorite that combines tender chicken breast, cubed potatoes, diced carrots, chopped onions, hard-boiled eggs and a delightful sweet-savory dressing. The said ingredients are all bound together with creamy mayonnaise and a touch of condensed milk.
Almond Jelly with Lychee is a refreshing dessert features wobbly almond jelly swimming in a pool of lychee syrup, offering a delightful textural contrast and bursts of tropical fruit flavor.

Adobo rice is a popular Filipino dish that combines the rich flavors of traditional adobo with steamed white rice. The dish features tender pieces of marinated meat (usually chicken or pork) simmered in a tangy sauce made from vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, and various spices.
Sprite is a classic, crisp lemon-lime soda. This refreshing drink is perfect for any meal.
Beef Morcon is a Filipino celebratory dish. This flavorful dish features tender beef flank stuffed with a savory center of sausages, cheese, vegetables, and then braised in a rich sauce.
Roast Pork with Mushroom Gravy is a romatic Filipino comfort food. Succulent roast pork is bathed in a savory and earthy mushroom gravy, making it a perfect balance of tender meat and rich flavors.

Supreme Baked Chicken is a Filipino twist on a classic.  Tender and juicy chicken breasts are baked to perfection, then topped with a creamy yogurt or sour cream marinade for a touch of tangy goodness.

Creamed Seafood Casserole is a decadent Filipino comfort food.  Chunks of shrimp, fish, or a variety of seafood are bathed in a rich and creamy sauce, creating a delightful combination of textures and flavors.

A Caesar salad is a classic green salad made with romaine lettuce and croutons, dressed with a flavorful combination of lemon juice, olive oil, egg yolks, Worcestershire sauce, anchovies, garlic, Dijon mustard, Parmesan cheese, and black pepper.
The Filipino Choco Flan Cake, also known as “Leche Flan Cake” or “Chocolate Leche Flan,” is a delightful fusion of two beloved desserts—leche flan and chocolate cake
Bright yellow rice seasoned with annatto, garlic, and other spices, often served alongside grilled meats and seafood.
Pepsi offers a refreshing and slightly sweeter taste than Coke. Some describe it as having a more pronounced sweetness.

Lengua con Champignon is a delightful Filipino dish that features velvety-soft ox tongue in a rich and creamy mushroom sauce. The tongue is slow-cooked until tender, resulting in melt-in-your-mouth tenderness
Pork in Casserole is a comforting and hearty dish that combines tender diced pork with a medley of flavorful ingredients.

Chicken with Bacon and Cheese is a dish that features chicken breast wrapped in savory bacon and topped with melted cheese. This delightful combination of flavors offers a satisfying and indulgent experience, perfect for those who enjoy a fusion of creamy and smoky tastes.

Fish Fillet with Tartar Sauce is a dish featuring crispy, golden-brown fish fillets served with a tangy tartar sauce. The delicate, flaky fish is perfectly complemented by the creamy sauce, which adds a zesty kick.

Shrimp Potato Salad is a dish that combines tender shrimp with creamy potatoes, tossed in a rich and flavorful dressing. This refreshing salad is perfect for those who enjoy a blend of seafood and hearty potatoes, offering a delightful mix of textures and tastes in every bite.
Blueberry Cheesecake is a delightful dessert that combines the richness of creamy cheesecake with the burst of sweet-tart blueberries.
Royal is known for its refreshing citrus flavor. Whether enjoyed on a hot day or paired with classic Filipino dishes, Royal Tru-Orange remains a beloved choice for Filipinos

Beef with Oyster Sauce is a popular dish made with tender slices of beef cooked with a savory and slightly sweet oyster sauce-based gravy. It features thinly sliced beef stir-fried with vegetables like onions and spring onions, then combined with a sauce made from oyster sauce, soy sauce, and other seasonings

Chinese Style Pork Steak is a dish that features tender pork steaks marinated in a savory blend of soy sauce, garlic, and various spices, then pan-fried to perfection. This flavorful dish combines the richness of the pork with the aromatic seasoning, offering a taste of Chinese cuisine that's both hearty and delicious.

Chicken Asado is a dish that features succulent chicken pieces simmered in a rich, savory tomato sauce infused with soy sauce, garlic, onions, and a touch of sweetness. This classic Filipino dish offers a delightful balance of flavors, making it a comforting and hearty meal perfect for any occasion.

Dish Name: Fish Fillet with Sweet and Sour Brown Sauce
Description: Fish Fillet with Sweet and Sour Brown Sauce is a dish that features crispy fish fillets topped with a flavorful sweet and sour sauce. The sauce is made with a combination of brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, and ketchup, creating a tangy and savory flavor profile.

Chopsuey with Quail Eggs is a dish that combines a colorful mix of vegetables such as cabbage, carrots, bell peppers, and snap peas, stir-fried with quail eggs and a savory sauce. This dish offers a delightful crunch from the vegetables and a burst of flavor from the quail eggs, making it a nutritious and satisfying meal.

White Salad is a refreshing dish made with a combination of white-colored ingredients such as diced chicken breast, boiled eggs, cauliflower florets, and mayonnaise, creating a creamy and flavorful salad.
Mountain Dew is a carbonated soft drink known for its bright green color and citrus flavor. It is often described as having a bold and refreshing taste, with a combination of sweetness and tanginess.
Tenderloin Tips with Mushroom Sauce is a dish that features tender pieces of beef tenderloin, pan-seared to perfection and served with a rich mushroom sauce.

Savory Croquettes are crispy fried patties made from a mixture of mashed potatoes, ground meat (such as beef, chicken, or ham), and various seasonings. The mixture is typically shaped into patties, coated in breadcrumbs, and deep-fried until golden brown and crispy.
Pastel de Pollo is a traditional Latin American dish that consists of layers of shredded chicken, vegetables (such as peas and carrots), and a creamy sauce, all encased in a flaky pastry crust.

Steamed Lapu-Lapu with Brown Sauce is a dish featuring a whole Lapu-Lapu (grouper fish) steamed to perfection and served with a savory brown sauce. The fish is typically seasoned with garlic, ginger, and soy sauce before steaming, which helps to enhance its natural flavors.

Dish Name: Lettuce Salad with Thousand Island dressing
Description: Lettuce Salad with Thousand Island Dressing is a classic salad featuring crisp lettuce leaves mixed with tomatoes, cucumbers, onions, and other vegetables, topped with a creamy Thousand Island dressing.

Pandan Crepe is a type of crepe made with pandan (screwpine) extract, which gives it a vibrant green color and a unique, fragrant flavor. The crepe batter is made with flour, eggs, milk, sugar, and pandan extract, then cooked into thin, delicate crepes.
Sarsi is a Filipino soft drink known for its unique sarsaparilla flavor. It is a dark-colored carbonated drink that is sweet and slightly herbal in taste, often compared to root beer.

Morconcitos are a type of Spanish sausage made from minced pork that is seasoned with spices such as paprika, garlic, and salt. The mixture is typically stuffed into natural casings and then twisted or tied into small links.
Pastel de Lengua with Crust is a dish that features beef tongue (lengua) cooked until tender, then sliced and layered with a savory sauce, vegetables, and sometimes hard-boiled eggs.
Spanish Stuffed Chicken is a dish that features chicken breasts stuffed with a flavorful mixture of ingredients such as Spanish chorizo, Manchego cheese, roasted red peppers, and herbs.
Grilled Tanigue with Lemon Sauce is a dish that features tanigue (Spanish mackerel) fillets marinated in a mixture of lemon juice, olive oil, garlic, and herbs, then grilled to perfection.
Buttered Vegetables is a simple and delicious dish that features a variety of fresh vegetables, such as carrots, broccoli, and cauliflower, sautéed in butter until tender-crisp.
Mango Crepe is a delightful dessert made with thin, delicate crepes filled with sweet, ripe mango slices and topped with a drizzle of mango sauce or syrup.
Seven Up is a popular lemon-lime flavored carbonated soft drink. It is known for its crisp and refreshing taste, with a hint of citrus flavor.
Roast Beef is a classic dish featuring a large cut of beef, such as a sirloin or rib roast, that is seasoned with herbs and spices, then roasted in the oven until tender and cooked to perfection.
Pork Spareribs with Orange Glaze is a dish that features tender pork spareribs marinated in a flavorful mixture of orange juice, soy sauce, garlic, and ginger, then roasted or grilled to perfection.
Garlic Fried Chicken is a dish that features tender chicken pieces marinated in garlic, soy sauce, and other seasonings, then coated in flour or breadcrumbs and fried until golden brown and crispy.

Dish Name: Pan Grilled Lapu-Lapu in Olive Oil
Description: Pan-Grilled Lapu-Lapu in Olive Oil is a dish that features Lapu-Lapu (grouper fish) fillets seasoned with herbs, spices, and olive oil, then grilled in a pan until cooked through and slightly charred.

Chicken Macaroni Salad is a popular Filipino dish that combines cooked macaroni pasta with shredded chicken, mayonnaise, and a variety of vegetables and fruits such as carrots, pineapple, and raisins. The salad is typically seasoned with salt, pepper, and sugar, and chilled before serving.
Chocolate Mousse is a decadent dessert made from whipped cream or egg whites, sugar, and melted chocolate. The mixture is chilled until set, creating a light and airy texture.

Coke Zero is a sugar-free, zero-calorie version of Coca-Cola. It is sweetened with artificial sweeteners such as aspartame and acesulfame potassium to provide a similar taste to regular Coca-Cola without the calories.

Beef Mechado is a Filipino dish that features beef stewed in a flavorful tomato-based sauce with onions, garlic, and bell peppers. The beef is typically marinated in soy sauce and calamansi juice (or lemon juice) to enhance its flavor before being simmered until tender.

Meatballs with Cheese Sauce is a dish that features savory meatballs made from ground meat (such as beef or pork) mixed with breadcrumbs, herbs, and spices, then baked or fried until golden brown and cooked through.

Chicken a la Orange is a dish that features tender chicken breasts cooked in a sweet and tangy orange sauce. The sauce is made from orange juice, orange zest, honey or sugar, vinegar, and spices such as ginger and garlic, which are simmered together until thickened.

Fish Fillet Florentine is a dish that features tender fish fillets topped with a creamy spinach and cheese sauce. The fish fillets are typically baked or grilled until flaky and then topped with the sauce, which is made from sautéed spinach, onions, garlic, cream, and Parmesan cheese.
Potato, Ham, and Pineapple Salad is a refreshing and flavorful dish that combines boiled potatoes, diced ham, and chunks of pineapple with a creamy dressing.

Mango Cake is a delicious dessert made with layers of sponge cake, whipped cream, and fresh mango slices. The sponge cake layers are soaked in a light syrup to keep them moist, and then filled and frosted with whipped cream and mango puree.

Diet Coke is a sugar-free and calorie-free version of Coca-Cola. It is a popular choice for those looking to reduce their sugar intake or manage their weight while still enjoying a carbonated soft drink.

Old-Fashion Beef Pie is a hearty and comforting pie filled with tender beef, vegetables, and rich gravy, all encased in a flaky pastry crust. This classic dish is a favorite for its savory flavors and satisfying texture.

Gourmet Pork Chops features tender pork chops marinated in a flavorful blend of herbs, spices, and olive oil, then grilled or baked to perfection. The result is a juicy and flavorful dish that is sure to impress.

Embutido is a Filipino-style meatloaf made with ground pork, raisins, eggs, and various spices, all wrapped in a sheet of aluminum foil and steamed or baked until cooked through. It is a popular dish for special occasions and gatherings.

Grilled Tanigue with Sesame-Lime Marinade features tanigue (Spanish mackerel) fillets marinated in a flavorful mixture of sesame oil, lime juice, garlic, and soy sauce, then grilled to perfection. The marinade adds a delicious depth of flavor to the fish, making it a standout dish.

Baked Spaghetti with Cheese Sauce is a comforting and indulgent dish that features spaghetti noodles baked in a creamy cheese sauce until bubbly and golden brown. It is a favorite for its rich and satisfying flavors.
Fruit Salad is a refreshing dish that features a mix of fresh fruits such as apples, bananas, grapes, and oranges, combined with a creamy dressing made from whipped cream or yogurt.
Mug Root Beer is a popular carbonated soft drink known for its bold and sweet flavor. It is often enjoyed chilled and served in a frosty mug for maximum refreshment.

Kare-Kare is a Filipino stew made with oxtail, tripe, and vegetables, cooked in a rich peanut sauce and flavored with shrimp paste. This hearty dish is a favorite for its savory and nutty flavors, often served with a side of bagoong (fermented shrimp paste) for added depth of flavor.

Chicken Pork Adobo is a classic Filipino dish made with chicken and pork simmered in a tangy and savory sauce made from vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, and spices. The dish is known for its rich and flavorful sauce, which is perfect for spooning over steamed rice.

Rellenong Bangus is a Filipino dish made from milkfish (bangus) stuffed with a mixture of ground pork, vegetables, and spices. The fish is then fried until crispy and golden brown, creating a dish that is both flavorful and visually appealing.

Shrimp Rolls are a type of Filipino spring roll made with a thin wrapper filled with a mixture of ground shrimp, vegetables, and spices. The rolls are then deep-fried until crispy and served with a sweet and tangy dipping sauce.

Lumpiang Sariwa with Peanut Sauce is a Filipino version of fresh spring rolls made with a variety of vegetables, shrimp, and sometimes pork, wrapped in a thin crepe-like wrapper. The rolls are served with a sweet and savory peanut sauce, making them a delicious and healthy snack or appetizer.
Leche Flan is a rich and creamy Filipino dessert made with egg yolks, condensed milk, and evaporated milk. The mixture is steamed until set and then chilled until firm.
Fruit Soda is a refreshing carbonated beverage flavored with a mix of fruit juices, offering a sweet and tangy taste that is perfect for quenching thirst on a hot day.

Beef Caldereta is a Filipino stew made with tender beef, potatoes, carrots, and bell peppers, simmered in a rich and flavorful tomato-based sauce with liver paste and spices. This hearty dish is a favorite for its savory and spicy flavors.

Lechon Paksiw is a Filipino dish made with leftover lechon (roast pig) that is simmered in a tangy and sweet sauce made from vinegar, soy sauce, sugar, and spices. The dish is known for its rich and flavorful sauce, which complements the tender meat perfectly.
Chicken Barbeque features marinated chicken pieces grilled to perfection, offering a smoky and flavorful taste that is perfect for a backyard barbecue or a casual meal with family and friends.

Rellenong Hipon is a Filipino dish made with whole shrimp stuffed with a mixture of ground pork, vegetables, and spices, then deep-fried until crispy. The dish is known for its savory flavors and crunchy texture.

Lumpiang Ubod is a Filipino spring roll made with heart of palm (ubod) strips, vegetables, and sometimes shrimp or pork, wrapped in a thin crepe-like wrapper and served with a sweet and savory dipping sauce.

Buko Jello is a refreshing dessert made with young coconut (buko) strips suspended in a gelatin made from coconut water and sweetened condensed milk. The dessert is chilled until set and served cold, offering a light and sweet treat.
Sprite Zero is a sugar-free and calorie-free version of Sprite, a lemon-lime flavored carbonated soft drink.

Paella Valenciana is a Spanish rice dish made with saffron-infused rice, chicken, rabbit, vegetables, and sometimes seafood, all cooked together in a large, shallow pan to create a flavorful and aromatic dish that is perfect for sharing.

Creamy Loin Cordon Bleu features tender pork loin slices stuffed with ham and cheese, then breaded and fried until crispy and golden brown. The dish is then smothered in a creamy sauce, creating a rich and indulgent meal that is sure to satisfy.

Dates and Walnut Bars are a sweet and chewy dessert made with dates, walnuts, and oats, all bound together with a sticky mixture of honey and butter. The bars are baked until golden brown and then sliced into squares, making them a delicious and satisfying treat.

Buffalo Wings are deep-fried chicken wings coated in a spicy sauce made from hot sauce, butter, and other seasonings. They are typically served with celery sticks and blue cheese dressing, offering a combination of spicy, tangy, and creamy flavors.

Lechon Kawali is a Filipino dish made with crispy pork belly that is first boiled until tender, then deep-fried until golden and crispy. The result is a dish with a crispy exterior and a tender and flavorful interior, often served with a dipping sauce made from vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, and chili peppers.

Seafood Sotanghon is a Filipino noodle dish made with sotanghon (cellophane noodles) cooked in a savory broth with mixed seafood such as shrimp, squid, and fish, as well as vegetables like carrots, cabbage, and bell peppers. The dish is flavored with soy sauce, garlic, and onions, offering a comforting and hearty meal.

Grilled Salmon Filipino Style features salmon fillets marinated in a mixture of soy sauce, calamansi juice (or lemon juice), garlic, and spices, then grilled until tender and flaky. The marinade infuses the salmon with a savory and tangy flavor, making it a delicious and healthy dish that is perfect for seafood lovers.

Pandan Lumpia with Candied Walnut is a dessert made with pandan-flavored wrappers filled with a mixture of sweetened shredded coconut and candied walnuts. The lumpia is then fried until crispy and golden brown, creating a delicious and indulgent treat that is perfect for satisfying a sweet tooth.

Special Leche Flan is a Filipino dessert made with egg yolks, condensed milk, evaporated milk, and sugar, which are cooked together until thickened and then poured into molds and steamed until set. The result is a rich and creamy flan with a caramelized sugar topping, offering a decadent and satisfying treat.

Buco Pandan Salad is a Filipino dessert made with young coconut (buko) strips, pandan-flavored gelatin cubes, and sweetened cream, all mixed together to create a refreshing and creamy salad. The dessert is often served chilled and garnished with additional coconut strips and pandan leaves, making it a popular choice for parties and special occasions.

Dish Name: Beef with Oyster Sauce and Flower Broccoli
Description: Beef with Oyster Sauce and Flower Broccoli features tender slices of beef stir-fried with oyster sauce, garlic, and ginger, then mixed with blanched flower broccoli (gai lan) to create a flavorful and nutritious dish. The dish is often served with steamed rice, offering a satisfying and wholesome meal.

Steamed Lapu-Lapu is a Filipino dish made with whole lapu-lapu (grouper fish) steamed with soy sauce, ginger, garlic, and other seasonings until tender and flavorful. The fish is often garnished with sliced onions and cilantro before serving, offering a simple yet delicious dish that highlights the natural flavors of the fish.

Stuffed Chicken is a dish where chicken breasts are filled with a savory stuffing, which can include a variety of ingredients such as cheese, vegetables, herbs, and spices. The stuffed chicken is then baked or grilled until the chicken is cooked through and the stuffing is hot and bubbly

Delicious Szechuan Shrimp is a spicy and flavorful Chinese dish featuring shrimp stir-fried with Szechuan peppercorns, garlic, ginger, and dried red chilies. The dish is known for its bold and spicy flavor profile, balanced with a hint of sweetness from hoisin sauce or sugar.

Chinese Spring Rolls are a popular appetizer in Chinese cuisine made with a thin wrapper filled with vegetables, such as cabbage, carrots, and mushrooms, as well as sometimes with meat, such as pork or shrimp.
Pork Roast is a dish made with a cut of pork, such as a pork loin or shoulder, that is seasoned with herbs, spices, and sometimes a marinade, then roasted until tender and juicy.

Chinese Fresh Lumpia is a Filipino version of spring rolls made with a soft and thin crepe-like wrapper filled with a mixture of vegetables, such as cabbage, carrots, and beans sprouts, as well as sometimes with shrimp, pork, or chicken.

Chocolate Dates and Walnut Square is a sweet and indulgent dessert made with dates, walnuts, and chocolate, all mixed together and pressed into a square shape. The dessert is rich and chewy, with the sweetness of the dates and the crunch of the walnuts complementing the chocolate flavor perfectly.

Heavenly Pot Roast is a classic comfort food dish made with beef roast, carrots, potatoes, onions, and garlic, slow-cooked until tender in a savory broth. The dish is hearty and flavorful, with the meat becoming melt-in-your-mouth tender and infused with the rich flavors of the vegetables and broth.

Callos is a Spanish-inspired dish made with ox tripe, chorizo, and chickpeas cooked in a rich tomato-based sauce flavored with paprika and other spices. The dish is hearty and flavorful, with the tripe becoming tender and soaking up the delicious flavors of the sauce. Callos is often served with rice or crusty bread.
Stuffed Seabass on Salsa Verde features seabass fillets stuffed with a flavorful mixture of herbs, breadcrumbs, and spices, then baked until the fish is tender and flaky.

Shrimp Potato and Fruit Salad is a refreshing and flavorful salad made with boiled shrimp, diced potatoes, and a variety of fruits such as apples, grapes, and pineapple, all mixed together with a creamy dressing.

Rellenong Manok is a Filipino dish made with a whole chicken stuffed with a mixture of ground meat, vegetables, and spices, then roasted until the chicken is cooked through and the stuffing is hot and flavorful.

Dish Name: Pork Ribs with Orange Sauce and Potato Relish
Description: Pork Ribs with Orange Sauce and Potato Relish features tender pork ribs marinated in a tangy orange sauce, then grilled or roasted until the meat is tender and caramelized.

Buco Jello is a refreshing and light dessert made with coconut-flavored gelatin and young coconut (buko) strips, all set in a sweet and fragrant syrup. The dessert is often served chilled and makes for a delightful and tropical treat, perfect for cooling off on a hot day.

Hito Pampango is a Filipino dish made with grilled or fried hito (catfish) marinated in a mixture of vinegar, garlic, and spices, then grilled or fried until the fish is cooked through and crispy. The dish is often served with a side of green mango salad, adding a fresh and tangy contrast to the rich and savory fish.

Chicken Inasal is a Filipino dish made with marinated chicken pieces grilled until charred and cooked through. The chicken is marinated in a mixture of vinegar, soy sauce, garlic, and other spices, giving it a savory and tangy flavor. Chicken Inasal is often served with rice and a dipping sauce made with vinegar, soy sauce, and spices.

Capampangan Menudo is a Filipino stew made with pork, liver, potatoes, carrots, and bell peppers, cooked in a savory tomato-based sauce. The dish is hearty and flavorful, with the meat and vegetables becoming tender and soaking up the delicious flavors of the sauce. Capampangan Menudo is often served with rice and is a popular dish for gatherings and special occasions.

Laing is a Filipino dish made with dried taro leaves cooked in coconut milk with chili peppers, shrimp paste, and other seasonings. The dish is rich, creamy, and flavorful, with the taro leaves absorbing the coconut milk and spices, creating a delicious and aromatic dish. Laing is often served with rice and is a popular comfort food in the Philippines.

Pork Lard Binagoongan is a Filipino dish made with pork belly cooked in a savory and tangy shrimp paste sauce, flavored with garlic, onions, tomatoes, and chili peppers. The dish is rich and flavorful, with the pork belly becoming tender and soaking up the delicious flavors of the sauce

Bibingkang Malagkit is a Filipino dessert made with glutinous rice (malagkit), coconut milk, and sugar, which are cooked together until thick and creamy. The mixture is then spread into a pan, topped with coconut milk and sometimes with latik (coconut curds), and baked until set, creating a sweet and sticky rice cake that is perfect for snacking or dessert.

Tropical Fruits as dessert is a simple yet refreshing dessert made with a variety of tropical fruits such as mangoes, pineapples, papayas, and bananas, which are typically served chilled and sometimes garnished with a drizzle of honey or a sprinkle of coconut flakes. This dessert is light, healthy, and bursting with tropical flavors.

Mirinda drink is a carbonated soft drink with a fruity flavor, known for its refreshing and sweet taste. It is often served chilled and is popular for its vibrant color and fruity aroma, making it a refreshing choice for quenching thirst and enjoying a fruity beverage

Mechadong Antiguo is a Filipino dish made with beef or pork liver and heart, cooked in a rich tomato-based sauce with garlic, onions, bell peppers, and spices. The dish is savory and flavorful, with the liver and heart becoming tender and absorbing the delicious flavors of the sauce. Mechadong Antiguo is often served with rice and is a popular dish in Filipino cuisine.

Bopis is a spicy Filipino dish made with minced pork or beef lungs and heart, sautéed with garlic, onions, and spices such as chili peppers and paprika. The dish is known for its bold and spicy flavor, with the meat becoming tender and flavorful from the long cooking process.

Paella Filipina is a Filipino version of the Spanish paella, made with glutinous rice (malagkit) cooked in coconut milk and flavored with annatto (achuete), garlic, onions, bell peppers, and various meats and seafood such as chicken, pork, shrimp, and mussels.

Lechon Manok is a Filipino dish made with whole chicken marinated in a blend of spices, including lemongrass, garlic, soy sauce, and calamansi (Filipino lime), then roasted or grilled until the skin is crispy and the meat is tender and juicy.

Pork Adobo with Talangka is a Filipino dish made with pork braised in a savory mixture of soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, bay leaves, and black peppercorns, with the addition of talangka (crab roe) to enhance its flavor. The dish is rich and flavorful, with the crab roe adding a unique and creamy texture to the classic adobo.

Prawn Manticado is a luxurious dish made with large prawns cooked in a rich and creamy sauce made with butter, cream, and a touch of brandy or white wine. The dish is elegant and flavorful, with the prawns becoming tender and infused with the creamy, buttery sauce.
Lumpiang Isda with Quesong Puti is a Filipino dish made with fish fillets and quesong puti (white cheese) wrapped in a lumpia (spring roll) wrapper and deep-fried until golden brown and crispy.

Ube Palitaw is a Filipino dessert made with glutinous rice cakes flavored with ube (purple yam) and coated in grated coconut, sugar, and sesame seeds. The dish is colorful and sweet, with the soft and chewy rice cakes providing a delightful contrast to the crunchy and nutty coating.

Coke Light is a popular carbonated soft drink known for its crisp and refreshing taste with fewer calories. It offers the same great flavor as regular Coke but with a lighter, less sweet profile, making it a popular choice for those looking to enjoy a soft drink with reduced calories.

Seafoods Tempura is a Japanese dish consisting of a variety of seafood, such as shrimp, squid, and fish, lightly battered and deep-fried until golden and crispy. The dish is often served with a dipping sauce made of soy sauce, mirin, and dashi.

Vegetables Tempura is a Japanese dish made with a variety of vegetables, such as sweet potatoes, bell peppers, and eggplants, lightly battered and deep-fried until crispy. The dish is light and flavorful, with the vegetables retaining their natural sweetness and texture, often served with a dipping sauce made of soy sauce, mirin, and dashi.

Tuna Sashimi is a Japanese dish featuring thin slices of raw tuna served with soy sauce, wasabi, and pickled ginger. The dish highlights the freshness and natural flavor of the tuna, providing a clean and delicate taste that is both refreshing and satisfying.

Stuffed Crab Claws are a luxurious dish made with crab claws filled with a mixture of crab meat, shrimp, and herbs, then breaded and deep-fried until golden and crispy. The dish is elegant and flavorful, with the tender crab meat and shrimp complementing the crispy exterior.

Sake Steamed Chicken is a Japanese-inspired dish made with chicken pieces steamed with sake (Japanese rice wine), soy sauce, ginger, and garlic, resulting in tender and flavorful meat. The dish is light and aromatic, with the sake adding a subtle sweetness and depth of flavor to the chicken.

Beef Teriyaki is a Japanese dish made with thin slices of beef marinated in a sweet and savory teriyaki sauce made of soy sauce, mirin, and sugar, then grilled or broiled until caramelized and tender. The dish is flavorful and delicious, often served with steamed rice and vegetables.
Grilled Pink Salmon is a simple yet flavorful dish made with fresh pink salmon fillets seasoned with herbs, lemon juice, and olive oil, then grilled until the fish is tender and slightly charred.

Buco Salad is a Filipino dessert made with shredded young coconut (buco), mixed with condensed milk, cream, and often combined with various fruits such as pineapple, cherries, and nata de coco. This creamy and refreshing salad is served chilled.

Beef Bulgogi is a Korean dish made with thinly sliced beef marinated in a mixture of soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, garlic, and green onions, then grilled or stir-fried until tender and caramelized. The dish is sweet and savory, served with rice.

Shrimp and Squid Bulgogi is a Korean dish featuring shrimp and squid marinated in a savory-sweet bulgogi sauce made of soy sauce, garlic, sesame oil, and sugar. The seafood is then grilled or stir-fried until tender and flavorful.
Pandan Chicken is a Thai-inspired dish made with chicken pieces marinated in a mixture of soy sauce, garlic, and pandan leaves, then wrapped in pandan leaves and deep-fried until golden and aromatic.

Nonya Paella is a fusion dish combining Spanish paella with Nonya (Peranakan) flavors, made with rice cooked in a rich broth of coconut milk, turmeric, and spices, along with chicken, prawns, and vegetables. The dish is vibrant and aromatic, offering a unique blend of Spanish and Southeast Asian flavors.

Chili Crabs is a popular Southeast Asian dish made with crabs cooked in a spicy and tangy chili sauce made of tomatoes, chili paste, garlic, and vinegar. The dish is rich and flavorful, with the sweetness of the crab meat balancing the heat of the sauce. It is often served with steamed buns or rice.

Steamed Pork with Lotus Leaves is a Chinese dish made with marinated pork pieces wrapped in lotus leaves and steamed until tender. The lotus leaves infuse the pork with a subtle, earthy aroma, and the dish is often served with rice, making it a fragrant and delicious meal.

Korean Sotanghon is a Korean-inspired dish made with glass noodles (sotanghon) stir-fried with vegetables, meat, and a savory sauce made of soy sauce, garlic, and sesame oil. The dish is light and flavorful, often garnished with sesame seeds and green onions.

Beef Lengua in Mushroom Sauce is a Filipino dish made with tender slices of beef tongue cooked in a creamy mushroom sauce. The dish is rich and flavorful, with the beef tongue becoming melt-in-your-mouth tender, and the mushroom sauce adding a savory depth of flavor.

Shrimp Pecante Pasta is an Italian-inspired dish featuring pasta tossed with shrimp in a spicy tomato sauce made with chili peppers, garlic, and olive oil. The dish is flavorful and has a pleasant heat, with the tender shrimp complementing the al dente pasta.

Dish Name: Grilled Tanigue in Buttered Lemon Sauce
Description: Grilled Tanigue in Buttered Lemon Sauce is a Filipino dish made with tanigue (Spanish mackerel) fillets grilled to perfection and drizzled with a rich butter and lemon sauce. The dish is light and flavorful, with the tangy lemon sauce balancing the richness of the butter and enhancing the natural taste of the fish.

Dish Name: Toss Green Salad with Caesar Dressing
Description: Toss Green Salad with Caesar Dressing is a classic salad made with fresh greens, such as romaine lettuce, tossed in a creamy Caesar dressing made with anchovies, garlic, lemon juice, and Parmesan cheese.

Turtle Cake is a decadent dessert made with layers of chocolate cake, caramel, and pecans, often topped with a rich chocolate ganache. The cake is moist and indulgent, with the caramel and pecans adding a delightful crunch and flavor contrast to the rich chocolate layers.

RC Cola is a popular carbonated soft drink known for its crisp and refreshing taste. It offers a sweet and bubbly experience, often enjoyed chilled. RC Cola is a classic beverage choice for many, providing a satisfying alternative to other cola brands.

Pastel de Lengua is a Filipino dish made with tender beef tongue (lengua) cooked in a creamy sauce, then baked with a pastry crust. The dish is rich and flavorful, with the creamy sauce and tender tongue creating a luxurious filling, encased in a flaky, golden crust.

Mixed Sausage Pasta is a hearty Italian-inspired dish featuring a variety of sausages, such as Italian sausage, chorizo, and bratwurst, tossed with pasta in a rich tomato or creamy sauce. The dish is flavorful and satisfying, with the different sausages adding depth and complexity to the sauce

Rainbow Fish is a visually stunning dish made with fish fillets arranged in a colorful presentation, often incorporating a variety of vegetables or a vibrant sauce. The dish is as pleasing to the eyes as it is to the palate, with the fresh fish and vegetables creating a harmonious and delicious meal.

Dish Name: Fillet Mignon with Demi Glace Sauce
Description: Fillet Mignon with Demi-Glace Sauce is a luxurious dish featuring a tender cut of beef fillet mignon, cooked to perfection and served with a rich demi-glace sauce made from reduced veal stock, wine, and aromatics.

Prawn in Chili Garlic Sauce is a spicy and flavorful dish made with succulent prawns cooked in a sauce of chili peppers, garlic, and soy sauce. The dish is bold and aromatic, with the heat of the chili peppers and the savory garlic complementing the sweetness of the prawns.
Potato Salad is a classic side dish made with boiled potatoes mixed with mayonnaise, mustard, and often incorporating ingredients such as hard-boiled eggs, celery, onions, and pickles.

Crema de Fruta is a Filipino dessert made with layers of sponge cake, custard, gelatin, and assorted fruits such as peaches, pineapples, and cherries. The dessert is light and refreshing, with the combination of creamy custard, tender cake, and fruity flavors.

Halayang Ube is a traditional Filipino dessert made from purple yam (ube) cooked with coconut milk and condensed milk until it becomes a thick, smooth paste. The dish is sweet and rich, with the unique flavor and vibrant color of the ube making it a beloved treat, often enjoyed as a snack or dessert, sometimes topped with cheese.

Tanigue Steak Filipino Style is a dish featuring tanigue (Spanish mackerel) fillets marinated in a mixture of soy sauce, calamansi (Filipino lime), garlic, and pepper, then grilled or pan-fried until tender and slightly charred.

Crispy Pata is a Filipino dish made with deep-fried pork knuckles that are marinated, boiled, and then fried to achieve a crispy skin and tender, juicy meat inside. The dish is typically served with a vinegar-based dipping sauce
Creamy Fettuccine is an Italian pasta dish featuring fettuccine noodles tossed in a rich and creamy sauce made with butter, heavy cream, and Parmesan cheese.

Honeyed Barbecue is a dish featuring meat, often pork or chicken, marinated in a sweet and savory sauce made with honey, soy sauce, garlic, and spices, then grilled or baked until caramelized and tender.

Mango Bars are a sweet dessert made with a buttery crust and a layer of mango filling, often topped with a crumbly streusel. The bars are fruity and refreshing, with the natural sweetness of the mangoes shining through, making them a perfect treat for mango lovers and a delightful addition to any dessert spread.

Dish Name: Baked Beef Ribs with Mushroom Gravy
Description: Baked Beef Ribs with Mushroom Gravy is a hearty dish featuring tender beef ribs baked to perfection and smothered in a rich mushroom gravy. The dish is savory and comforting, with the beef ribs becoming melt-in-your-mouth tender, and the mushroom gravy adding a deep, earthy flavor.

Pan-Grilled Lapu-Lapu in Olive Oil is a Filipino dish made with Lapu-Lapu (grouper) fillets pan-grilled with olive oil, garlic, and herbs. The dish is light and flavorful, with the delicate fish complemented by the aromatic olive oil and garlic.
Baked Lasagna is an Italian classic featuring layers of pasta, rich meat sauce, creamy béchamel, and melted cheese, all baked together until bubbly and golden.
Chicken Tips with Demi-Glace Sauce is a gourmet dish featuring tender chicken pieces cooked in a rich demi-glace sauce made from reduced veal stock, wine, and aromatics.

Dish Name: Prawns and Squid in Ink Risotto
Description: Prawns and Squid in Ink Risotto is a sophisticated dish featuring prawns and squid cooked in a creamy risotto made with squid ink, which gives the dish a striking black color and a rich, briny flavor.

Pork Barbecue is a popular dish made with skewers of marinated pork grilled to perfection. The marinade typically includes soy sauce, vinegar, garlic, sugar, and spices, giving the pork a savory and slightly sweet flavor.

Macaron is a delicate French confection made with almond flour, egg whites, and sugar, filled with various flavored ganaches, buttercreams, or jams. The macaron is crisp on the outside and chewy on the inside.
